fe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 445<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 6:34:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/allencraig1/Syll4.jpg width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Head of Granhex Drah (monk red headband quest)</span><hr size=1> The head will be affected by TLC.<br><br>Corrupt guard faction can be raised by delivering the crate of defective arrows from guard weleth in North Qeynos, to the woodshop in South Qeynos, but giving the receipt to Lietenant Dagarok instead of back to Guard Weleth.<br><br>The gnoll isn't rare at all, so you might just hunt other stuff in the zone and check back from time to time, or every time you pass through the zone, etc.  I see him there about 1/3 of the time when I pass through that zone.<br><br>Syllestrae Silverblade<br>Warchanter of Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kendrikfv>kendrik fv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 9:01:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> thanks</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info, Syllestrae. Time to make the SK trek I guess. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 11:20:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ghanex Drah</span><hr size=1> He's not on the same cycle as putrids, IIRC.  He spawns in the SouthEast corner by one of those tower thingies.<br><br>This was made *really* easy after the Paw &quot;takeover.&quot;<br><br><br><br> <p>--Antoin Nolouj &lt;League of Shadows&gt;<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyntercrystalbow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wynter Crystalbow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 2:29:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ghanex Drah</span><hr size=1> Personally I don't mind the easy part too much.  Will still likely need a group.  It's the sash I'm worried about.  Getting down to Ekeros is not much fun, needing a lot of luck and patience, and playing with Priest Amiaz isn't a walk in the park either.  Didn't know the putrids gave Corrupt hits.  Doesn't bother me too much but nice to know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 4:02:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bloodsabres</span><hr size=1> The putrids are on Bloodsabres faction, as is Lord Grimrot.  Killing them will provide minor hits to your Corrupt Q Guard faction.<br><br>However the Corrupt Q Guards are repairable (the message delivery quest in Freeport is one way.) but it is TEDIOUS, and you'll need to be at least apprehensive to the rogues (which isn't uncommon, IIRC.)<br><br> <p>--Antoin Nolouj &lt;League of Shadows&gt;<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 10:59:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bah</span><hr size=1> Who cares about corrupt guard faction? You can be dead kos and still have a fairly easy time getting around, especially 30+.  There's one guy near the lake in North Qeynos (Lieutenant? Colonel?) that's 50+ and you gotta watch out for, but hte others are all low level...<br><br>Kyrial <p><center><i><a href=mailto:kyrial_moonlight@lycos.com>Kyrial Moonlight</a><BR><font color=white>A light shines upon us all.</font></I><P>Wyrd Windwalker.  Kyrial Darkflame.</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 11:08:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Be careful who you damn straight out...</span><hr size=1> I think the one you're talking about (Lt. Dagarok) harm touches.<br><br>I don't like being KOS in part of a city.  ALL of it however can have its moments...<br><br> <p>--Antoin Nolouj &lt;League of Shadows&gt;<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulindril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lindril</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 7:14:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Head of Granhex Drah (monk red headband quest)</span><hr size=1> I know exactly what causes Ghanex to spawn.. He has a particular Place Holder (a Putrid Skeleton)  That spawns on a certain Cycle a bit longer than the other Putrids.  Kill the PH, over and over and wait.  HE WILL Despawn in approx 30 mins.  How do I know this?  Hours of Grimrot camping and watching  lol.  If you want me to tell you the loc of the PH, contact Andlie in game.<br><br> <p><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://home.attbi.com/~2emiller/LinAndlieSig1.jpg"><br><i><font face="Tahoma" size="3" color="#9933FF">Preserver ofValhalla's Pyre, Quellious      Priestess of Mischief,Firiona Vie </font></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kendrikfv>kendrik fv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 9:07:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Granhex</span><hr size=1> Well, today Jorma spent the better part of 4 hours sittin' around the undead camp waiting for granhex with no luck. There was even a level 40+ cleric there as well waiting for Grimrot so my victory would have been pretty much assured. No Granhex, bah. I will contact you Andlie for the location.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 3:17:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ghanex ..</span><hr size=1> .. is a pushover at 20 and still not TLC'd at that level.  I killed him as I ran by a few weeks ago. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukilder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 11:35:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Granhex</span><hr size=1> a helped a monk friend get the head at level 17.  We just killed every single skeleton (putrid and otherwise) since we did not know exactly which one was the place holder.  In about an hour maybe less he spawned and attacked.  he was not to difficult.<br><br>Finding the 2 high shamans has been considerably more difficult since we don't have any druid/ranger friends of high enough level and with the patience to comb south karana with us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 2:42:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Granhex</span><hr size=1> This npc has become rare fairly recently. About a month ago I think, apparently to balance out the monk epic. The head is definetly TLC'd. My monk buddy had to find that out the hard way.<br><br>I also heard a rumer that his head no longer drops all the time and has been rated &quot;uncommon&quot;. Can anyone confrim this?<br><br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 2:44:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=